motley-cue (0.4.3-1) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  [ Marcus Hardt ]
  * Initial go for packageing
  * Packaging for Debian Buster and Bullseye, Ubuntu Bionic and Focal, and CentOS 8
  * reload nginx config on install
  * Add support for CentOS 7
  * Add example for pooled accounts in config
  
  [ Diana Gudu ]
  * New version number
  * Install config files in /etc
  * Add nginx proxy for gunicorn
  * Changed default port in nginx to 8080
  * Bug fixes
  * Add latest feudalAdapter version (chage fix)
  * Flexible authorisation: per OP auth, individual users possible, admin auth
  * Improve logging
  * Add support for OPs that do not release JWT ATs
  * Use flaat v0.14.2 and feudalAdapter v0.3.101
  * Fixes for getting issuer from AT/userinfo with AT (via flaat v0.14.5)
  * Fixes for admin actions and iss representation
  * Disable assurance checking by default
  * Include fixes in feudal for Python 3.6 support
  * Add testing
  * Add sphinx docs and publish to github pages
  * Some fixes and openapi validations
  * Add support for flaat 1.0.0
  * Add support for LDAP backend (feudalAdapter 0.4.0)
  * Add audience-based authorisation
  * Add support for additional_groups in feudal conf
  * Add flaat 1.0.1 -> jwt verification fixes
  * Add feudalAdapter 0.4.2 -> home base config
  * New feature: support access tokens longer than 1k with one-time tokens
  * Add flaat 1.0.2 -> google support fix
  * Add feudalAdapter 0.4.4 -> fix group name shortening for unix backend
  * Add feudalAdapter 0.4.5 -> revert name shortening and fix duplicate unix groups
  * Add feudalAdapter 0.5.0 -> approval workflow
  * Add flaat 1.1.5 -> fixes and support for new EGI OP
  * Fix #49 one-time tokens header parse
  * Add feudalAdapter 0.5.2 -> group naming related fixes
  * Add new EGI OP in default motley_cue.conf
  * Add feudalAdapter 0.5.3
  * fix default paths to token db and keyfile

